Hi -- the behavior you're observing relates to the [client router cache](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/building-your-application/caching#router-cache).

If you'd like to disable the client router cache so that every request hits the server, you can disable it by modifying your `next.config.js` as follows:

```js
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const nextConfig = {
  experimental: {
    staleTimes: {
      dynamic: 0,
    },
  },
}

module.exports = nextConfig
```

You can learn more about this configuration option [here](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/next-config-js/staleTimes).

